OL,5, At the Lycee Mariam market in Kabul,   
OL,6, known for its long row of stalls       
OL,7, selling women's clothing, news of the  
OL,8, Taliban's latest decree had not yet    
OL,9, filtered down by the afternoon.        
OL,11,FSome of those browsing the shops wore  
OL,12,Fthe all-encompassing blue burka that   
OL,13,Fthe Taliban enforced during their first
OL,14,Fstint in power in the 1990s. Others,   
OL,15,Fhowever, had scarves covering their    
OL,16,Fhair, but their faces uncovered.       
OL,18,F"Even when you go on pilgrimage to     
OL,19,FSaudi Arabia you don't have to cover   
OL,20,Fyour face," one pointed out.           
